    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1967a"/>, p. 166, n. <citedRange>6</citedRange> (ph.) 
                    (= <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, p. <citedRange>78</citedRange></bibl> (ph.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>000430</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#marengo2010b"/>, p. <citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, p. <citedRange>70</citedRange></bibl>, whence <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>65.2030</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#antonini2016"/>, pp. <citedRange>45-46</citedRange></bibl> and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/> <citedRange>2017.638</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ας"><seg part="F"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/>ας</seg></name></persName> <orig>Χ</orig><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/>ας <orig>Χ</orig></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#gasperini1967a"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ΑΜΨ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Intraduisible.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمه بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>If we follow Gasperini's interpretation of the fourth letter, it is the third occurrence in Cyrenaica of a trident-shaped letter.
                In <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr110100</ref> and in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr001920</ref>, it is used as a chi, whereas the cross-shaped chi 
                    was the most frequent in the region. <bibl><ptr target="#marengo2010b"/></bibl> has shown that this rare shape is of Rhodian origin. The letter before it 
                    might not be a mu and its shape fits a san perfectly. So we propose to divide those poor letters into a name end and a word (or name) beginning.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
